## 4. MÃ‰THODOLOGIE EN 5 Ã‰TAPES {#mÃ©thodologie}

### **Ã‰TAPE 1 : CALCULER LA CAPACITÃ‰ RÃ‰ELLE**

**Objectif :** DÃ©terminer ce que l'Ã©quipe PEUT rÃ©ellement faire

#### **a) Standards de ProductivitÃ© (HypothÃ¨ses)**

| RÃ´le | MÃ©trique | Standard Annuel | Source |
|------|----------|-----------------|--------|
| **SDR** | SQO Created | 85 SQO/an (7/mois) | Bridge Group benchmarks |
| **AE** | SQO Won | 22 SQO/an (~2/mois) | CalculÃ© du budget ratio |
| **AE** | MRR Won | 7,500â‚¬/an (625â‚¬/mois) | CalculÃ© du budget ratio |

**Note :** Ces standards sont des **hypothÃ¨ses** Ã  valider avec actuals 2024 de Brevo

#### **b) Ajustements Individuels**

**1. Ramp Factor (diffÃ©renciÃ© SDR vs AE)**

**SDR (6 mois to full productivity) :**
```
M1-2:  30% (onboarding, training)
M3-4:  60% (premiÃ¨res SQO)
M5-6:  85% (quasi fully ramped)
M7+:  100% (fully ramped)
```

**AE (12 mois to full productivity) :**
```
M1-3:  25% (shadow, discovery calls)
M4-6:  50% (premiÃ¨res closes)
M7-9:  75% (pipeline construit)
M10-12: 90% (presque full)
M13+:  100% (fully ramped)
```

**Rationale :** AE plus long car cycle de vente + pipeline building

**2. Performance Tier**

| Tier | Multiplier | Distribution |
|------|-----------|--------------|
| **A-players** (top 20%) | 120% | ~20% Ã©quipe |
| **B-players** (mid 60%) | 100% | ~60% Ã©quipe |
| **C-players** (bottom 20%) | 80% | ~20% Ã©quipe |

**3. Working Time**
- **85%** (toutes rÃ©gions simplifiÃ©es)
- = 220 jours travaillÃ©s / 260 jours ouvrÃ©s
- Prend en compte : congÃ©s (20j), fÃ©riÃ©s (10j), maladie (5j), formation (5j)

#### **c) Formule de CapacitÃ©**

```
CapacitÃ© Annuelle Individuelle = 
    Base Standard (85 SQO ou 7,500â‚¬)
    Ã— Ramp Factor
    Ã— Performance Factor  
    Ã— Working Time (0.85)
```

**Exemple : Julia Clark (AE NorAm, M4, B-player)**
```
CapacitÃ© = 7,500â‚¬ Ã— 0.50 (M4-6) Ã— 1.00 (B) Ã— 0.85
         = 3,188â‚¬ MRR/an
         = 266â‚¬ MRR/mois
```

#### **d) AgrÃ©gation par Ã‰quipe**

```
CapacitÃ© Ã‰quipe = SUM(CapacitÃ©s Individuelles)
```

Utiliser SUMIFS pour filtrer par rÃ©gion/rÃ´le

---

### **Ã‰TAPE 2 : APPLIQUER DES BUFFERS INTELLIGENTS**

**Objectif :** Ajouter marges de sÃ©curitÃ© pour absorber la variabilitÃ©

#### **Architecture 3 Niveaux**

**Niveau 1 - Monthly Buffers (SaisonnalitÃ©)**

| Mois | Buffer | Rationale |
|------|--------|-----------|
| Janvier | +15% | Reprise post-holidays, ramping lent |
| FÃ©vrier | +10% | Normalisation |
| Mars | +5% | Stabilisation |
| Avril-Juillet | 0% | Performance standard |
| AoÃ»t | +5% | PÃ©riode vacances |
| Septembre-Novembre | 0% | Standard |
| DÃ©cembre | -5% | Push de fin d'annÃ©e |

**Niveau 2 - Regional Buffers (BasÃ© sur CV)**

| RÃ©gion | CV | Buffer | Logique |
|--------|-------|--------|---------|
| **FR** | 22% | 7% | CV faible â†’ Buffer faible |
| **DACH** | 36% | 12% | CV moyen â†’ Buffer moyen |
| **NorAm** | 39% | 12% | CV moyen-Ã©levÃ© |
| **ROW** | 55% | **17%** | CV Ã©levÃ© â†’ Buffer Ã©levÃ© |

**Formule empirique :**
```
Buffer = f(CV)

Si CV < 25%  â†’ Buffer 5-7%
Si CV 25-35% â†’ Buffer 10-12%
Si CV > 35%  â†’ Buffer 15-17%
```

**Niveau 3 - Metric Buffers (ComplexitÃ©)**

| MÃ©trique | Buffer | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| **SQO Created** (SDR) | +5% | DÃ©pend des leads inputs (hors contrÃ´le SDR) |
| **SQO Won** (AE) | +10% | VariabilitÃ© conversion |
| **MRR Won** (AE) | +15% | Deal size ET conversion fluctuent |

**Logique :** Plus de variables incontrÃ´lables = Plus de buffer

#### **Formule Budget AjustÃ©**

```
Budget AjustÃ© = Budget Base 
                Ã— (1 + Monthly Buffer) 
                Ã— (1 + Regional Buffer) 
                Ã— (1 + Metric Buffer)
```

**Exemple - NorAm Q1 MRR :**
```
Base :           156,125â‚¬
Monthly (Q1) :   +15% = +23,419â‚¬
Regional :       +12% = +18,735â‚¬
Metric (MRR) :   +15% = +23,419â‚¬

Budget AjustÃ© :  220,892â‚¬
```

---

### **Ã‰TAPE 3 : RÃ‰CONCILIER BUDGET vs CAPACITÃ‰**

**Objectif :** Choisir le quota final rÃ©aliste

#### **Formule de DÃ©cision**

```
Quota Final = MIN(
    Budget AjustÃ© (avec buffers),
    CapacitÃ© Ã— 1.15 (stretch factor)
)
```

**Stretch Factor 1.15 :**
- 15% au-dessus de la capacitÃ© "confortable"
- Standard industrie pour quotas ambitieux mais atteignables
- Balance entre ambition (croissance) et rÃ©alisme (attainment)

#### **Exemple - NorAm Q1 MRR**

```
Budget AjustÃ© :        220,892â‚¬
CapacitÃ© Team :         38,250â‚¬/an
CapacitÃ© Q1 :            9,563â‚¬ (38,250 / 4)
Capacity Stretch :      10,997â‚¬ (9,563 Ã— 1.15)

DÃ©cision : MIN(220,892, 10,997) = 10,997â‚¬

â†’ On utilise la CAPACITÃ‰ (budget irrÃ©aliste)
```

#### **Gap Analysis Matrix**

| Gap Budget vs CapacitÃ© | Status | Action Requise |
|------------------------|--------|----------------|
| **< 10%** | âœ“ OK | Use capacity Ã— 1.15 |
| **10-20%** | âš ï¸ WARNING | Negotiate with Finance OR hiring plan |
| **> 20%** | ğŸš¨ ALERT | CRO/CFO meeting, adjust budget OR aggressive hiring |

**RÃ©sultats NorAm :**
- Gap : -95% (budget demande 23x la capacitÃ©)
- Status : ğŸš¨ ALERT
- Action : Plan de recrutement +4 AE immÃ©diat OU ajuster budget -50%

#### **Documentation des DÃ©cisions**

Pour chaque rÃ©gion, documenter :
- Quota final retenu (capacity ou budget)
- Rationale (pourquoi ce choix)
- Gap identifiÃ©
- Action plan (hiring, budget adjust, ou accept low attainment)

---

### **Ã‰TAPE 4 : DISTRIBUER AUX INDIVIDUS**

**Objectif :** Allouer Ã©quitablement aux reps

#### **Formule MaÃ®tre**

```
Quota Mensuel Individuel = 
    (Team Quota / Team Size / 3 mois)
    Ã— Ramp Factor
    Ã— Performance Factor
    Ã— Seasonal Factor
```

#### **Seasonal Factors (mensuels)**

| Mois | Factor | Rationale |
|------|--------|-----------|
| Janvier | 0.95 | Reprise lente |
| FÃ©vrier-Novembre | 1.00 | Standard |
| DÃ©cembre | 1.10 | Push period |

#### **Exemple - Julia Clark (NorAm AE, Janvier)**

```
Team Quota Q1 :       10,997â‚¬
Team Size :           6 AE
Base Mensuel :        10,997 / 6 / 3 = 611â‚¬

Ajustements Julia :
- Ramp :              50% (M4)
- Performance :       100% (B-player)
- Seasonal :          95% (Janvier)

Quota Julia Janvier : 611 Ã— 0.50 Ã— 1.00 Ã— 0.95 = 290â‚¬ MRR
```

#### **Validation Rules (Automatiques)**

**Check 1 - Sum = Team Quota**
```
|SUM(Individual Quotas) - Team Quota| / Team Quota < 2%
```

**Check 2 - Fairness (CV < 40%)**
```
STDEV(Individual Quotas) / AVERAGE(Individual Quotas) < 0.40
```

**Check 3 - No Outliers (Ratio Max/Min < 2.0)**
```
MAX(Individual Quotas) / MIN(Individual Quotas) < 2.0
```

**Check 4 - Capacity Check**
```
Individual Quota < Individual Capacity Ã— 1.5
```

**Si validation Ã©choue :** Alerte + Blocage jusqu'Ã  correction

---

### **Ã‰TAPE 5 : TRACKER & AJUSTER**

**Objectif :** Monitor performance et rÃ©agir

#### **a) Simulation Actuals (pour dÃ©mo)**

```
Simulated Actual = Quota Ã— NORM.INV(RAND(), 0.85, 0.15)
```
- Moyenne : 85% attainment
- Ã‰cart-type : 15%

#### **b) Calcul Attainment**

**SDR (volume simple) :**
```
Attainment % = Actual SQO Created / Quota SQO Created
```

**AE (blended volume + valeur) :**
```
Attainment % = (Actual SQO Won / Quota SQO Won + Actual MRR Won / Quota MRR Won) / 2
```

**Status Logic :**
```
Si Attainment >= 100% â†’ âœ“ ON TRACK
Si Attainment 70-99%  â†’ âš ï¸ AT RISK
Si Attainment < 70%   â†’ ğŸš¨ CRITICAL
```

#### **c) Ajustement Mensuel (Exemple FÃ©vrier)**

**RÃ©sultats Janvier :**
- SDR : 77/85 SQO (91% attainment) â†’ Shortfall -8 SQO
- AE : 30/36 SQO (83% attainment) â†’ Shortfall -6 SQO
- AE : 3,370â‚¬/4,167â‚¬ MRR (81% attainment) â†’ Shortfall -797â‚¬

**Options d'Ajustement :**

**Option A - Spread Evenly (3 mois):**
```
Shortfall rÃ©parti sur Feb-Mar-Apr
SDR : +3 SQO/mois
AE : +2 SQO/mois + 266â‚¬ MRR/mois
```

**Option B - Focus FÃ©vrier (spike):**
```
Tout le shortfall sur FÃ©vrier
SDR : +8 SQO
AE : +6 SQO + 797â‚¬ MRR
```

**Option C - Graduated (RECOMMANDÃ‰):**
```
FÃ©vrier : +5 SQO SDR, +4 SQO AE, +450â‚¬ MRR (60% du gap)
Mars :    +2 SQO SDR, +1 SQO AE, +200â‚¬ MRR (25% du gap)
Avril :   +1 SQO SDR, +1 SQO AE, +147â‚¬ MRR (15% du gap)
```

**Rationale Option C :**
- Balance ambition et rÃ©alisme
- Ramping reps (Bob M4, Julia M5) attendu +30-40% productivitÃ©
- Top performers maintiennent momentum
- Laisse buffer si still underperform

**Option D - Accept Loss:**
```
Keep Feb-Dec as-is
Adjust annual targets H2
Accept 85% attainment global
```

